Sentencas: The commercialization of efficient and durable solid oxide fuel cells is hugely hindered due to the expensive and complex fabrication process.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: In this regard, the additive manufacturing technique, i.e., three-dimensional printing (3-D printing), has gained tremendous attention because of its ability to fabricate tunable functional ceramic layers with cost-effectiveness and mass customization.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: Therefore, in this work, the anode (NiO-ScSZ) and cathode (LSM) of the large-area SOFC (5 x 5 cm2) are printed using a direct-ink-writing (DIW) printer.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: The anode-functional and electrolyte layers are coated by spray and spin coating.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: The viscosity of the optimized anode and cathode inks are 5.85 Pa s and 0.97 Pa s, respectively.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: The electrochemical impedance and the performance of 3D-SOFC are investigated by supplying hydrogen and air.
Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell is 368 mW cm-2 at 800 degrees C.

Titulo: Development of highly efficient and durable large-area solid oxide fuel cell by a direct-ink-writing three-dimensional printer

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, the long-term cell test under galvanostatic mode (j = 0.5 A cm-2) at 700 degrees C for 100 h and thermal cycling between 400 and 700 degrees C concludes that the 3D-SOFC exhibits exceptional stability with a voltage loss of 0.845% h-1 and thermomechanical durability.
